Ya Ning, president of iQiyi Pictures Photo: Courtesy of iQiyiiQiyi Pictures, China's streaming giant iQiyi's film studio, released the slate for their upcoming movies at its annual World Conference on Friday. Six original films covering the genres of comedy, romance, crime and war will hit theaters in the coming years. Titles include Welcome to the Beartown, Spring with Fever, No. 1 Tank and A Wedding Invitation 2. Adapted from the hit Thai film ATM, Welcome to the Beartown stars Chinese actor Zhu Yawen and actress Sandrine Pinna, while No.1 Tank tells a story based on the true events of the battle of Nanjing in 1937. Additionally, iQiyi announced it will work with actress Bai Baihe and musician Jonathan Lee on the Super Music IP Project, which aims to collect story ideas for Lee's four singles and produce them into four streaming dramas as well as a film. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Actress Liu honored with Hollywood Walk of Fame starDelegation of HUST attends alumni gala in Los AngelesChinese driving Vegas growth